bush philosopher
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a self-trained philosopher living and working in bush; a moralising or philosophically inclined bushman (bush - may have a derog. sense as in bush baptist, carpenter 2, lawyer; or merely a locative sense as in bush carpenter 1, bush doctor, preacher. That is it may mean `an amateur philosopher perniciously fond of moralising'; or `one who lives in the bush and is an amateur philosopher').
